The paper proposes a novel filter unit for deep neural networks that is specifically designed for image classification and semantic segmentation tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on improving the performance of deep neural networks by reducing the number of parameters and achieving faster convergence, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the spatial distribution of the filter units, which could be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper could also be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) category, as semantic segmentation is a task that involves understanding the meaning of language.
